We say that G_1 is the edge-side and G_2 the split-side of the composition. Furthermore, we say that xy is the replaced edge of G_1 and that z is the split vertex of G_2. Finally we say that G is a k-Ore graph if it can be obtained from copies of K_k and repeated Ore-compositions.

